                                        <span class="ez-toc-section" id="C0_vs_C6_Performance"></span>
                                        <h3>C0 vs C6 Performance</h3>
                                        
                                        <p>Mathematical modeling of Chiori's damage output reveals significant differences between her C0 and C6 potential:</p>
                                        
                                        <div class="wp-block-table">
                                            <table>
                                                <thead>
                                                    <tr>
                                                        <th>Configuration</th>
                                                        <th>Personal DPS</th>
                                                        <th>Team DPS Contribution</th>
                                                        <th>Notes</th>
                                                    </tr>
                                                </thead>
                                                <tbody>
                                                    <tr>
                                                        <td>C0 Sub-DPS (Husk)</td>
                                                        <td>24,560</td>
                                                        <td>18-22% of total</td>
                                                        <td>Off-field role, consistent damage</td>
                                                    </tr>
                                                    <tr>
                                                        <td>C0 Sub-DPS (Troupe)</td>
                                                        <td>22,340</td>
                                                        <td>16-20% of total</td>
                                                        <td>More versatile but lower ceiling</td>
                                                    </tr>
                                                    <tr>
                                                        <td>C6 Main DPS (Husk)</td>
                                                        <td>38,750</td>
                                                        <td>30-35% of total</td>
                                                        <td>On-field carry potential</td>
                                                    </tr>
                                                    <tr>
                                                        <td>C6 Main DPS (Troupe)</td>
                                                        <td>35,960</td>
                                                        <td>28-32% of total</td>
                                                        <td>More consistent, less conditional</td>
                                                    </tr>
                                                </tbody>
                                            </table>
                                        </div>
                                        
                                        <p>C6 provides approximately a 38-42% increase in Chiori's personal damage output compared to C0, transforming her from a strong Sub-DPS into a viable Main DPS that can compete with other established carries in the appropriate team compositions.</p>
                                        
                                        <span class="ez-toc-section" id="Artifact_Set_Comparisons"></span>
                                        <h3>Artifact Set Comparisons</h3>
                                        
                                        <p>Our analysis of various artifact sets shows clear performance differences:</p>
                                        
                                        <ul>
                                            <li><strong>4pc Husk of Opulent Dreams:</strong> Consistently provides 8-12% higher damage than alternative sets in scenarios where Chiori's DEF scaling is maximized. The 24% DEF and 24% Geo DMG bonus (at full stacks) directly enhances her Skill and Burst damage.</li>
                                            <li><strong>4pc Gladiator's Troupe:</strong> While providing ~10% less damage than Husk, this set offers more consistent performance without the need to maintain stacks. It's particularly competitive for players with excellent substats or for quick-swap team rotations.</li>
                                            <li><strong>2pc Husk + 2pc Archaic Petra:</strong> This combination performs within 5% of 4pc Husk in scenarios where maintaining Husk stacks is difficult. The unconditional Geo DMG bonus is valuable in all situations.</li>
                                            <li><strong>2pc Husk + 2pc Emblem of Severed Fate:</strong> For energy-hungry rotations or teams without a second Geo character, this combination helps maintain Burst uptime at the cost of ~7% damage compared to 4pc Husk.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        
                                        <span class="ez-toc-section" id="Weapon_Rankings"></span>
                                        <h3>Weapon Rankings</h3>
                                        
                                        <p>Based on our mathematical models, Chiori's weapons rank as follows:</p>
                                        
                                        <h4>5-Star Weapons</h4>
                                        <ol>
                                            <li><strong>Primordial Jade Cutter:</strong> Offers the highest ceiling due to its CRIT Rate substat and HP% bonus that converts to ATK. ~100% theoretical performance.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Light of Foliar Incision:</strong> Performs at ~97% of PJC's potential with a CRIT DMG substat and Normal Attack bonuses that benefit C6 Chiori.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Key of Khaj-Nisut:</strong> ~95% performance relative to PJC, providing substantial HP and EM bonuses that work well for teams utilizing Crystallize reactions.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Haran Geppaku Futsu:</strong> ~93% performance, with strong Normal Attack bonuses for C6 and Elemental DMG% that benefits her Skill and Burst.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Mistsplitter Reforged:</strong> ~92% performance, with excellent Elemental DMG bonuses but stacks that can be difficult to maintain for off-field Chiori.</li>
                                        </ol>
                                        
                                        <h4>4-Star Weapons</h4>
                                        <ol>
                                            <li><strong>Favonius Sword:</strong> The Energy generation makes this an excellent team support option, performing at ~82% of PJC's damage while providing valuable utility.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Blackcliff Longsword:</strong> ~80% performance with a CRIT DMG substat that scales well with refinements and stacks.</li>
                                            <li><strong>The Black Sword:</strong> ~78% performance with CRIT Rate and Normal Attack bonuses that benefit C6 Chiori.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Harbinger of Dawn (R5):</strong> ~76% performance when its passive can be maintained, making it a strong F2P option.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Cinnabar Spindle:</strong> ~73% performance with DEF scaling that synergizes with her kit, though limited by its low base ATK.</li>
                                        </ol>
                                        
                                        <p>These rankings assume optimal artifacts and team compositions. Individual performance may vary based on specific substats and team synergies.</p>
                                        <span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span>
                                        
