                                    <h2 class="wp-block-heading">
                                        <span class="ez-toc-section" id="Mono_Geo_Teams"></span>
                                        Mono Geo Teams<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span>
                                    </h2>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Itto-Noelle-Gorou-Chiori-Geo.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60611" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Itto-Noelle-Gorou-Chiori-Geo.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Itto-Noelle-Gorou-Chiori-Geo-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>
                                                    <strong>Itto / Noelle — Gorou — Chiori — Flex</strong>
                                                </strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>Itto is one of the best on-field DPS units to have in a Mono Geo team with Chiori. Ushi counts as a Geo Construct, so he lets the fourth team slot be somewhat flexible. Additionally, Chiori has highly consistent Geo Particle generation, which helps significantly reduce Itto’s and Gorou’s ER requirements. It is also possible for Chiori to use her Burst every rotation in Mono Geo Itto teams since it requires only a few ER% substats.</p>
                                    <p>Noelle is an alternative to Itto, but she requires a Geo Construct character like Zhongli or Albedo in the fourth team slot since neither Noelle nor Gorou create constructs.</p>
                                    <h3 class="wp-block-heading">Example Teams</h3>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Itto-Gorou-Chiori-Zhongli.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60610" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Itto-Gorou-Chiori-Zhongli.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Itto-Gorou-Chiori-Zhongli-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Itto — Gorou — Chiori — Zhongli</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>Zhongli is still a highly recommended option in Itto-Chiori teams since his Geo RES Shred and shield (for Geo Resonance) significantly increase the team’s damage.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>
                                        Zhongli hED &gt;Gorou Q &gt;Chiori (Q) 2[E] &gt;Gorou E &gt;Itto <a href="https://keqingmains.com/q/itto-quickguide/#Combos" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">combo</a>
                                    </p>
                                    <div style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Itto-Gorou-Chiori-Bennett.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60616" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Itto-Gorou-Chiori-Bennett.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Itto-Gorou-Chiori-Bennett-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Itto — Gorou — Chiori — Bennett</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>Despite Itto’s and Chiori’s DEF% scaling, Bennett’s Flat ATK buff is still good. Since Chiori’s Skill doesn’t snapshot, she can make use of Bennett’s 4pc Noblesse Oblige buff even if he takes the field after her. Note that this team lacks a shielder.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>
                                        Gorou EQ &gt;Bennett tEQ &gt;Chiori (Q) 2[E] &gt;Itto <a href="https://keqingmains.com/q/itto-quickguide/#Combos" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">combo</a>
                                    </p>
                                    <div style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Noelle-Gorou-Chiori-Albedo.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60615" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Noelle-Gorou-Chiori-Albedo.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Noelle-Gorou-Chiori-Albedo-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Noelle — Gorou — Chiori — Albedo</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>Neither Noelle nor Gorou create Geo Constructs, so Albedo or Zhongli are recommended in this Mono Geo team if Chiori is C0. Chiori and Albedo’s combined Geo Particle generation significantly reduces Noelle’s ER requirements.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>Gorou EQ &gt;Albedo E &gt;Chiori (Q) 2[E] &gt;Noelle E Q N3D N3 &gt;Gorou E &gt;Noelle 3[N3D] N2
                                    </p>
                                    <div style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
                                    <h2 class="wp-block-heading">
                                        <span class="ez-toc-section" id="Ningguang-Chiori_Teams"></span>
                                        Ningguang-Chiori Teams<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span>
                                    </h2>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ningguang-Chiori-Flex-Flex.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60622" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ningguang-Chiori-Flex-Flex.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ningguang-Chiori-Flex-Flex-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Ningguang — Chiori — Flex — Flex</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>Ningguang is a viable on-field DPS who can allow shorter 17s rotations depending on her teammates’ cooldowns. Her teams with Chiori tend to perform best in single-target scenarios. The two flex slots should be off-field DPS units like Fischl, Yelan, or Furina, or off-field supports like Bennett, Zhongli, or Gorou.</p>
                                    <h3 class="wp-block-heading">Example Teams</h3>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ningguang-Chiori-Fischl-Bennett.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60621" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ningguang-Chiori-Fischl-Bennett.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ningguang-Chiori-Fischl-Bennett-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Ningguang — Chiori — Fischl — Bennett</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>This is a very strong Ningguang team, especially if Fischl is C6. Bennett’s buffs benefit the entire team. The rotation below allows Fischl to snapshot Bennett’s buff, but you can use Bennett immediately before Ningguang to maximize her use of his buffs.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>
                                        Bennett EQ &gt;Fischl E/Q &gt;Ningguang C E &gt;Chiori D (Q) 2[E] &gt;Ningguang D Q E C N2C &gt;Bennett E &gt;Ningguang N2C<br>
                                        <br>Fischl alternates between her Skill and Burst over multiple rotations. Ningguang and Chiori should dash through Ningguang’s Skill to receive the Geo DMG% buff before using their abilities.
                                    </p>
                                    <div style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ningguang-Chiori-Furina-Bennett.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60613" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ningguang-Chiori-Furina-Bennett.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ningguang-Chiori-Furina-Bennett-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Ningguang — Chiori — Furina — Bennett</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>Another strong Ningguang team with a 20s rotation to accommodate Furina. Bennett’s on-field healing prevents Harbinger of Dawn from being viable on Chiori in this team.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>
                                        Furina ED Q &gt;Bennett EQ &gt;Ningguang C E &gt;Chiori D (Q) 2[E] &gt;Ningguang D Q E C N2C &gt;Bennett E &gt;Ningguang C N2C<br>
                                        <br>Ningguang and Chiori should dash through Ningguang’s Skill to receive the Geo DMG% buff before using their abilities.
                                    </p>
                                    <p></p>
                                    <h2 class="wp-block-heading">
                                        <span class="ez-toc-section" id="Navia-Chiori_Teams"></span>
                                        Navia-Chiori Teams<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span>
                                    </h2>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Navia-Chiori-Flex-Flex.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60619" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Navia-Chiori-Flex-Flex.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Navia-Chiori-Flex-Flex-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Navia — Chiori — Pyro / Electro / Cryo / Hydro</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>Navia benefits greatly from Chiori’s consistent Geo application and particle generation. However, Navia does not create a Geo Construct and strongly prefers two Pyro, Electro, Cryo, or Hydro teammates, which prevents another Geo teammate. Nonetheless, C0 Chiori is still great with Navia, and C1 Chiori only makes this pairing better.</p>
                                    <p>Chiori does not generate Geo Particles on Skill cast, so she does not need to come before Navia in the rotation to prefunnel particles for Navia’s Burst.</p>
                                    <h3 class="wp-block-heading">Example Teams</h3>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Navia-Chiori-Fischl-Bannett.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60618" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Navia-Chiori-Fischl-Bannett.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Navia-Chiori-Fischl-Bannett-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Navia — Chiori — Fischl — Bennett</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>This is a very strong Navia team comparable to the version with Zhongli instead of Chiori. Since Chiori’s Skill does not snapshot, she can take advantage of Bennett’s 4pc Noblesse Oblige buff even if she casts her Skill beforehand.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>Navia Q &gt;Bennett tEQ &gt;Chiori (Q) 2[E] &gt;Fischl E/Q &gt;Navia E N3D N2 E N3D N2 &gt;Bennett tE N1
                                    </p>
                                    <div style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Navia-Chiori-Furina-Kokomi.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60620" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Navia-Chiori-Furina-Kokomi.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Navia-Chiori-Furina-Kokomi-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Navia — Chiori — Furina — Kokomi</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>Furina provides a powerful DMG% buff, while Kokomi’s healing counteracts Furina’s teamwide HP drain. This team prefers a 20s rotation since Furina’s Skill, Kokomi’s Skill, and TTDS all have a 20s cooldown.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>Furina ED Q &gt;Navia Q &gt;Chiori (Q) 2[E] &gt;Kokomi E &gt;Navia E N3D N2 &gt;Kokomi Q N2D N2 &gt;Navia E N3D N2
                                    </p>
                                    <h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="Double-Geo-Off-Field-Core">
                                        <span class="ez-toc-section" id="Double_Geo_Off-Field_Core"></span>
                                        Double Geo Off-Field Core<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span>
                                    </h2>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Flex-Flex-Chiori-Zhongli.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60608" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Flex-Flex-Chiori-Zhongli.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Flex-Flex-Chiori-Zhongli-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Flex — Flex — Chiori — Zhongli / Geo</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>Chiori forms an excellent off-field core with Zhongli. He provides 20% Universal RES Shred, the strongest shield in the game, and a long-lasting Geo Construct.</p>
                                    <p>Chiori can also be paired with Albedo, since he provides strong off-field damage and the longest-lasting Geo Construct in the game. However, he does compete with Chiori’s weapon selection. Geo Traveler and off-field Ningguang are free-to-play alternatives in the core, but they don’t provide nearly as much utility as Zhongli or as much damage as Albedo.</p>
                                    <p>Her teammate’s Geo Constructs can be easily destroyed by bosses and large enemies, but they can be readily replaced thanks to short Skill cooldowns.</p>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Lyney-Bennett-Chiori-Zhongli.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60612" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Lyney-Bennett-Chiori-Zhongli.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Lyney-Bennett-Chiori-Zhongli-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Lyney — Bennett — Chiori — Zhongli</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>This Lyney team is incredibly easy to play. However, Chiori’s and Zhongli’s combined Geo application removes a Pyro aura, so Zhongli should place his pillar away from the enemy.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>
                                        Zhongli hED &gt;Chiori (Q) 2[E] &gt;Bennett tEQ &gt;Lyney 5[C] (Q/C) E<br>
                                        <br>Lyney should use his Burst every other rotation. When his Burst is down, he can use a sixth Charged Shot before casting his Skill.
                                    </p>
                                    <div style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ganyu-Shenhe-Chiori-Zhongli.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60609" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ganyu-Shenhe-Chiori-Zhongli.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Ganyu-Shenhe-Chiori-Zhongli-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Ganyu — Shenhe — Chiori — Zhongli</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>A Double Geo core with Zhongli enables a very simple yet effective Ganyu team. Chiori’s inclusion in this Mono Cryo archetype has several benefits: she enables Geo Resonance (which strengthens Zhongli’s shield) and deals good damage, all while maintaining low field time.</p>
                                    <p>This team does not require a fixed rotation, since you can refresh abilities as they come off cooldown. Still, an optimized rotation is shown below.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>Ganyu C &gt;Zhongli hED &gt;Chiori (Q) 2[E] &gt;Shenhe tEQ &gt;Ganyu E Q 3[C] &gt;Shenhe tE &gt;Ganyu C E C
                                    </p>
                                    <div style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Kokomi-Furina-Chiori-Albedo.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60617" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Kokomi-Furina-Chiori-Albedo.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Kokomi-Furina-Chiori-Albedo-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>
                                                    <strong>Kokomi — Furina — Chiori — </strong>
                                                    Albedo
                                                </strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>This is a very simple yet potent Double Hydro + Double Geo team with Kokomi as the on-field driver and healer to counteract Furina’s teamwide HP drain. Chiori’s Skill also takes full advantage of Furina’s teamwide DMG% buff, since the latter lasts for Chiori’s entire Skill duration. Kokomi should pick up Hydro Crystallize shards to maintain the Geo Resonance buff.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>Albedo E &gt;Kokomi E &gt;Furina ED Q &gt;Chiori (Q) 2[E] &gt;Kokomi Q 5[N3D]
                                    </p>
                                    <div style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Yelan-Xingqiu-Chiori-Zhongli.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60623" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Yelan-Xingqiu-Chiori-Zhongli.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Yelan-Xingqiu-Chiori-Zhongli-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Yelan — Xingqiu — Chiori — Zhongli</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>Another strong Double Hydro + Double Geo team, especially in single-target scenarios. Yelan can drive on-field to take advantage of her own DMG% buff and easily fit 2 Skill uses per rotation.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>Zhongli hED &gt;Xingqiu EDQ N1 &gt;Yelan E N1 Q N1 &gt;Chiori (Q) 2[E] &gt;Yelan 2[N3D] E 2[N3D]
                                    </p>
                                    <div style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Scara-Fischl-Chiori-Zhongli.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60614" width="768" height="212" srcset="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Scara-Fischl-Chiori-Zhongli.webp 1279w, https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Scara-Fischl-Chiori-Zhongli-768x211.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Wanderer — Fischl — Chiori — Zhongli</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>This is a potential Wanderer team without Faruzan. Fischl, Chiori, and Zhongli all have low field-time requirements and allow a 17s rotation. Wanderer uses his Burst when available.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>Zhongli hED &gt;Chiori (Q) 2[E] &gt;Fischl E/Q &gt;Wanderer E combo (Q)
                                    </p>
                                    
                                    <h2>
                                        <span class="ez-toc-section" id="C6_Team_Compositions"></span>
                                        C6 Team Compositions<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span>
                                    </h2>
                                    <p>Chiori's C6 constellation fundamentally transforms her gameplay, enabling her to function as a powerful on-field Main DPS. The following team compositions maximize her C6 potential:</p>
                                    
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Chiori-Zhongli-Albedo-Gorou.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60615" width="768" height="212"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Chiori (C6) — Zhongli — Albedo — Gorou</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>This Triple Geo team maximizes Chiori's C6 potential with Gorou providing DEF and Geo DMG bonuses, Zhongli offering universal RES shred, and Albedo contributing significant off-field damage while generating energy. With 3 Geo characters, Gorou's buffs reach their maximum potential, significantly boosting Chiori's damage.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>Zhongli hE &gt; Albedo E &gt; Gorou EQ &gt; Chiori E (hold) Q N1 CA (repeat N1 CA during burst duration)
                                    </p>
                                    
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Chiori-Xilonen-Bennett-Zhongli.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60616" width="768" height="212"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Chiori (C6) — Xilonen — Bennett — Zhongli</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>This team utilizes Xilonen's unique ability to enable plunge attacks, which interact exceptionally well with Chiori's C6. Bennett provides ATK buffs and healing, while Zhongli ensures survivability and RES shred. This composition yields some of the highest single-target damage potential for C6 Chiori.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>Zhongli hE &gt; Bennett Q &gt; Xilonen E Q &gt; Chiori E (hold) Q (Plunge spam within Xilonen's field)
                                    </p>
                                    
                                    <div class="wp-block-image">
                                        <figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized">
                                            <img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="https://keqingmains.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Chiori-Furina-Baizhu-Zhongli.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-60617" width="768" height="212"/>
                                            <figcaption class="wp-element-caption">
                                                <strong>Chiori (C6) — Furina — Baizhu — Zhongli</strong>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>This team leverages Furina's powerful damage buffs from her Salon Members while using Baizhu to manage HP and provide healing. Zhongli's shield ensures interruption resistance and RES shred. The team excels in sustained combat scenarios where Chiori can maximize her on-field time.</p>
                                    <p class="rot has-background" style="background-color:#0000001f">
                                        <strong>Sample Rotation</strong>
                                        <br>Zhongli hE &gt; Baizhu EQ &gt; Furina EQ &gt; Chiori E (hold) Q N1 CA (repeat)
                                    </p>
                                    
                                    <h2>
                                        <span class="ez-toc-section" id="Rotation_Analysis"></span>
                                        Rotation Analysis<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span>
                                    </h2>
                                    <p>C6 Chiori's rotations differ significantly from her C0 counterparts:</p>
                                    
                                    <ul>
                                        <li><strong>Standard C0 Rotation:</strong> Chiori performs E (tap) → Q → swap out, maintaining off-field damage through her Fashion Forward field</li>
                                        <li><strong>C6 Normal Attack Rotation:</strong> Chiori performs E (hold) → Q → N1 CA sequence, maximizing the Majestic Mountainscape Garment mechanic</li>
                                        <li><strong>C6 Plunge Rotation:</strong> With Xilonen, Chiori performs E (hold) → Q → Plunge attacks, achieving the highest damage ceiling</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    
                                    <p>Mathematical analysis shows that C6 Chiori's rotations provide approximately 40-45% more team DPS compared to her C0 rotations when properly executed with optimal teams.</p>
                                    
